# DAM Backtest Architecture

## 1. Project Overview
# DAMBT: Distributed Algorithmic Market BackTesting System

DAMBT is a distributed backtesting engine that separates:
1. metadata coordination (Coordinator)
2. distributed execution (Worker)
3. data storage (DataNode)

The system uses Raft to replicate metadata across coordinators.

## 2. System Architecture - Design Overview
## Architecture

DAMBT consists of three core components:

### Coordinator
- Manages metadata (chunks, jobs, results)
- Dispatches jobs to workers
- Uses Raft for fault-tolerant replication

### Worker
- Fetches chunk data from DataNodes
- Executes backtesting strategy
- Returns results to Coordinator

### DataNode
- Stores chunked market data
- Serves data via RPC

### Data Flow

Client → Coordinator → Workers → DataNodes
               ↑
              Raft
              (DG)

## 3. Failure Model
## Failure Handling

- Coordinator:
    Non-leader rejects writes
    Leader failure handled by Raft election

- Worker:
    Job fails if all replicas unreachable
    Partial retries handled by Coordinator

- DataNode:
    No replication yet (single-node storage)
    Data corruption not handled (future work)

## 4. Environment Setup

Requirements:
- Go 1.22+
- Linux / macOS / Windows

Verify:
- go version

## 5. Build Instructions

Build all packages:

make build

## 6. Test Instructions

# Run all tests:

make all

# Run final correctness tests:

make final

# Run performance tests:

make perf

# Run with debug logs:

make all-debug

## 7. Running the System
## Running DAMBT (Local Demo)

# Open multiple terminals:

# Terminal 1:
make run-datanode1

# Terminal 2:
make run-worker1

# Terminal 3:
make run-worker2

# Terminal 4+:
make run-coord0
make run-coord1
make run-coord2

## 8. Example Usage

# Example Workflow
1. Upload chunks
2. Register chunks
3. Submit job
4. Query result

## 9. Limitations

No persistent storage for Raft yet
No real market replay engine
No strategy plugin system
DataNode is single-replica

## 10. Future Work

Strategy plugin system (Python/C++)
Market replay engine
Data replication across DataNodes 
Persistent Raft state